[I] Friendly serial communication program

[T] minicom is a communication program which somewhat resembles the shareware
[T] program TELIX but is free with source code and runs under most unices.
[T] Features include dialing directory with auto-redial, support for UUCP-style
[T] lock files on serial devices, a seperate script language interpreter,
[T] capture to file, multiple users with individual configurations, and more.

[U] http://alioth.debian.org/projects/minicom/

